WEBVTT

00:00:12.750 --> 00:00:14.000
Kirito,

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:17.375
if you want her, take her with
your blade, your dual blades.

00:00:17.375 --> 00:00:21.292
If you can defeat me in combat,
you may take Asuna.

00:00:21.292 --> 00:00:23.625
But if you lose,

00:00:23.625 --> 00:00:26.583
you will join the Knights
of the Blood Oath.

00:00:30.208 --> 00:00:31.292
Very well.

00:00:31.375 --> 00:00:34.250
If you'd rather settle this with
swords, that's fine with me.

00:00:34.333 --> 00:00:36.458
Let's settle it with a duel.

00:00:36.625 --> 00:00:39.500
"October 20, 2024"       "Floor 75: Collinia"

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:41.667
Not many good seats left!

00:00:41.667 --> 00:00:43.958
"Living Legend, Heathcliff
VS Dual-wielding Demon, Kirito"
Hurry, hurry!

00:00:43.958 --> 00:00:47.375
You're such an idiot!
Why would you say that?

00:00:47.667 --> 00:00:49.833
Sorry. I'm sorry...

00:00:49.833 --> 00:00:52.792
I couldn't help it.
It was like tit for tat.

00:00:52.792 --> 00:00:58.292
When I saw your dual-wielding the other day,
I thought your strength was on another level.

00:00:58.875 --> 00:01:02.208
But the commander
has a unique skill too...

00:01:02.208 --> 00:01:04.875
Right. I've seen it several times.

00:01:05.250 --> 00:01:08.917
Divine Blade. It maximizes
attack and defense power.

00:01:08.917 --> 00:01:13.083
The attack is strong,
but that defense is incredible.

00:01:13.083 --> 00:01:17.917
No one has ever seen his HP bar
fall into the yellow zone.

00:01:18.583 --> 00:01:21.833
It's completely overpowered.

00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:23.958
I know.

00:01:23.958 --> 00:01:28.125
What'll you do? If you lose,
not only is my leave denied,

00:01:28.125 --> 00:01:31.833
but you'll have to join
the Knights of the Blood Oath.

00:01:31.833 --> 00:01:34.958
Well, I don't plan to lose easily.

00:01:47.375 --> 00:01:51.792
<i>The cowardly past that I'd acknowledged</i>

00:01:52.125 --> 00:01:57.625
<i>Still not understanding why,</i>

00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:08.542
<i>I stand behind myself, scared</i>
<i>Projecting reality onto today</i>

00:02:08.875 --> 00:02:13.875
<i>I've drawn so many skies</i>

00:02:14.208 --> 00:02:18.583
<i>This must be my fleeting heart</i>

00:02:18.917 --> 00:02:21.292
<i>Out of control</i>

00:02:21.625 --> 00:02:26.875
<i>In my dreams, this body soars so high</i>

00:02:27.208 --> 00:02:32.042
<i>And it can brush away any fears that cling to me</i>

00:02:32.375 --> 00:02:38.542
<i>Asleep inside me, these budding</i>
<i>feelings start to expand</i>

00:02:38.958 --> 00:02:42.542
<i>I realize this, weak as I am...</i>
<i>As long as I had you</i>

00:02:42.875 --> 00:02:47.833
<i>I could stay strong in this dark world</i>

00:02:48.167 --> 00:02:53.833
<i>My heart will dream a long dream forever</i>

00:02:54.750 --> 00:02:57.208
<i>I want to always be with you</i>

00:02:57.542 --> 00:03:02.917
<i>I'll give you everything I have...</i>

00:03:06.083 --> 00:03:10.083
"Crimson Killing Intent"

00:03:13.958 --> 00:03:16.167
I'm sorry, Kirito.

00:03:16.583 --> 00:03:19.667
I didn't realize things
would get like this.

00:03:19.667 --> 00:03:22.125
I'll be taking a cut of this.

00:03:22.125 --> 00:03:23.250
No.

00:03:23.250 --> 00:03:26.750
After the duel, you'll be
a member of our guild.

00:03:26.750 --> 00:03:29.333
I'll treat this as a mission.

00:03:33.542 --> 00:03:34.500
"Will you accept duel request?"
"Opponent: Heathcliff"
"Type: 1 vs. 1"

00:03:34.500 --> 00:03:35.875
"Normal Mode"
"Time-Limit Mode"
"One-Strike Mode"

00:04:07.542 --> 00:04:09.292
<i>He attacks with his shield?</i>

00:04:20.792 --> 00:04:23.000
Splendid reaction time.

00:04:23.375 --> 00:04:25.917
And your defense is impregnable.

00:04:36.500 --> 00:04:37.917
<i>Not yet...</i>

00:04:38.042 --> 00:04:40.125
<i>I can be even faster!</i>

00:04:51.500 --> 00:04:52.833
Kirito...

00:05:06.042 --> 00:05:07.625
<i>I can strike!</i>

00:05:16.750 --> 00:05:17.833
<i>What?</i>

00:05:45.167 --> 00:05:47.625
"October 22, 2024"       "Floor 50: Algade"

00:05:48.833 --> 00:05:52.750
D-Didn't I request
something that wasn't so flashy?

00:05:53.042 --> 00:05:55.875
It's one of the far less flashy ones.

00:05:56.125 --> 00:05:57.792
You look good.

00:06:01.542 --> 00:06:03.458
A guild, huh?

00:06:03.458 --> 00:06:06.625
I guess I dragged you into this, huh?

00:06:06.625 --> 00:06:12.375
No, it's a good chance. I was reaching
the limits of what a solo player could do.

00:06:12.375 --> 00:06:15.375
That does make me
feel better, but...

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:17.917
Hey, Kirito...

00:06:19.208 --> 00:06:24.375
I want you to tell me why
you avoid guilds and other people.

00:06:26.292 --> 00:06:31.292
It isn't just because you're a beta tester
or have a unique skill, right?

00:06:31.583 --> 00:06:33.958
You're a kind person after all.

00:06:38.250 --> 00:06:40.958
It was a long time ago.

00:06:40.958 --> 00:06:43.167
Over a year ago maybe...

00:06:43.375 --> 00:06:46.292
I did join a guild, just once.

00:06:47.500 --> 00:06:51.458
The guild was tiny. Even with
me there were only six of us.

00:06:51.458 --> 00:06:54.625
Its name was the Moonlit Black Cats.

00:06:54.625 --> 00:06:58.708
To be honest, their levels
were far lower than mine.

00:06:59.083 --> 00:07:04.042
So I think if I'd told them my
own level, they would've backed off.

00:07:04.042 --> 00:07:08.208
But I kept my true level
a secret and joined their guild.

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:14.458
The way they felt comfortable together
was something I craved back then.

00:07:14.875 --> 00:07:16.583
But one day...

00:07:26.792 --> 00:07:29.833
I was the one who
wiped out the entire guild.

00:07:29.833 --> 00:07:36.083
I could've convinced them of that trap's
danger if I hadn't hidden that I was a beater.

00:07:36.667 --> 00:07:40.542
All of them... Sachi... I killed them.

00:07:59.208 --> 00:08:00.833
I won't die.

00:08:02.917 --> 00:08:05.125
Because I'm the one

00:08:05.375 --> 00:08:07.792
who will protect you.

00:08:22.792 --> 00:08:25.542
"October 23, 2024"       "Floor 55: Grandzam"

00:08:25.542 --> 00:08:26.667
"October 23, 2024"       "Floor 55: Grandzam"
Training?

00:08:26.667 --> 00:08:28.083
That's right.

00:08:28.083 --> 00:08:31.208
You'll form a party
with me and one other,

00:08:31.208 --> 00:08:34.500
and we'll clear the dungeon
here on the 55th floor.

00:08:34.500 --> 00:08:37.667
Wait, Godfree. Kirito and I are...

00:08:37.667 --> 00:08:42.458
Even as the vice commander,
you cannot ignore the rules.

00:08:42.833 --> 00:08:47.042
And if he'll be joining us,
then as the forward commander,

00:08:47.042 --> 00:08:49.625
I must evaluate his skills.

00:08:49.625 --> 00:08:53.625
H-He's far stronger than you!
Way out of your league!

00:08:54.875 --> 00:08:59.000
Then we'll meet at
the western gate in 30 minutes!

00:09:04.792 --> 00:09:08.208
We finally had a chance to be alone...

00:09:08.208 --> 00:09:10.417
I'll be back soon.

00:09:10.417 --> 00:09:12.167
Wait here.

00:09:12.167 --> 00:09:13.292
Okay.

00:09:14.083 --> 00:09:15.583
Be careful.

00:09:21.667 --> 00:09:23.792
Hey, over here!

00:09:30.208 --> 00:09:31.583
What's this?

00:09:31.583 --> 00:09:34.792
From now on,
we're all in the same guild.

00:09:34.792 --> 00:09:39.417
I thought it would be a good time
for you to bury your differences.

00:09:42.458 --> 00:09:46.625
I'm sorry for causing
you trouble the other day.

00:09:47.083 --> 00:09:51.500
I will never act so rudely
again, so please forgive me.

00:09:51.708 --> 00:09:53.333
S-Sure...

00:09:53.583 --> 00:09:55.750
Right, cased closed.

00:09:57.333 --> 00:10:01.167
Today, I'd like to assess
how you react to danger,

00:10:01.167 --> 00:10:04.917
so I'll be taking all
of your crystals.

00:10:05.708 --> 00:10:08.542
--Even teleportation crystals?
--Yes.

00:10:17.458 --> 00:10:18.625
Fine.

00:10:22.750 --> 00:10:25.750
Right! Let's go, guys!

00:10:26.833 --> 00:10:28.000
--Yeah.
--Yeah.

00:10:30.167 --> 00:10:34.167
"Floor 55: Dungeon Entrance"

00:10:40.208 --> 00:10:43.250
Okay, we'll be taking a break here.

00:10:44.375 --> 00:10:46.792
I'll distribute the food.

00:11:21.375 --> 00:11:23.375
<i>Paralysis poison?</i>

00:11:34.042 --> 00:11:36.292
Wh-What is this?

00:11:36.500 --> 00:11:41.792
The one who brought this water
was you, wasn't it, Kuradeel?

00:11:41.792 --> 00:11:44.292
Hurry! An antidote crystal...

00:11:50.167 --> 00:11:54.417
Godfree, I always
knew you were an idiot,

00:11:54.417 --> 00:11:58.042
...but you really are
a certified numbskull.

00:12:00.042 --> 00:12:02.167
Wh-What are you doing?

00:12:09.958 --> 00:12:11.750
S-Stop it!

00:12:12.167 --> 00:12:13.917
Listen...

00:12:13.917 --> 00:12:15.958
Our party

00:12:17.625 --> 00:12:22.292
was attacked by a large gang of
criminal players out in the field!

00:12:22.542 --> 00:12:25.708
Though you both fought hard,
you were slain.

00:12:25.708 --> 00:12:31.792
I was alone but repulsed the criminals
in dazzling fashion and survived!

00:13:05.083 --> 00:13:06.458
Hey.

00:13:06.458 --> 00:13:12.292
Thanks to a brat like you,
I just killed an innocent bystander.

00:13:12.292 --> 00:13:16.333
For all that, you looked
happy enough...

00:13:16.333 --> 00:13:20.083
Why'd someone like you join
the Knights of the Blood Oath?

00:13:20.083 --> 00:13:23.292
You'd do better in
a criminal guild.

00:13:23.292 --> 00:13:27.583
That's an interesting thing
to say. You have sharp eyes.

00:13:29.000 --> 00:13:32.542
That's the murder guild,
Laughing Coffin's...

00:13:33.833 --> 00:13:37.500
That's where I got
this paralysis technique.

00:13:37.500 --> 00:13:39.375
Whoops.

00:13:39.542 --> 00:13:43.750
I'd better stop talking
or the poison will wear off.

00:13:43.750 --> 00:13:45.917
Time to finish you!

00:13:51.083 --> 00:13:53.708
<i>The poison's still in effect?</i>

00:13:59.125 --> 00:14:05.625
How does it feel? How does it feel,
knowing that you're about to die?

00:14:06.292 --> 00:14:09.000
Won't you tell me?

00:14:14.250 --> 00:14:15.750
<i>Am I...</i>

00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:18.625
<i>Am I going to die here?</i>

00:14:19.208 --> 00:14:21.000
Hey now...

00:14:21.375 --> 00:14:24.083
Come on, say something...

00:14:24.083 --> 00:14:26.417
You're really going to die!

00:14:49.500 --> 00:14:53.708
What's this? So you're
afraid of dying after all?

00:14:54.083 --> 00:14:55.583
That's right...

00:14:55.583 --> 00:14:58.083
I can't die yet!

00:14:59.833 --> 00:15:01.708
Is that so?

00:15:01.708 --> 00:15:04.208
That's the way I like it!

00:15:13.417 --> 00:15:15.125
Die! Die!

00:15:15.417 --> 00:15:19.667
Die!

00:15:32.667 --> 00:15:33.833
Heal!

00:15:36.083 --> 00:15:37.875
I made it...

00:15:38.083 --> 00:15:40.958
I made it, God...

00:15:41.333 --> 00:15:43.167
I made it.

00:15:46.417 --> 00:15:49.542
I was watching
your position on the map.

00:15:49.542 --> 00:15:54.750
There was no response from Godfree,
so I thought something might've happened...

00:15:55.375 --> 00:15:59.125
You're alive.
You're alive, right, Kirito?

00:15:59.125 --> 00:16:01.625
Yeah, I'm alive...

00:16:05.583 --> 00:16:09.167
Hold on. I'll end this right away.

00:16:11.708 --> 00:16:14.917
L-Lady Asuna, this was just training.

00:16:14.917 --> 00:16:17.458
Right, it was a training accident...

00:16:20.417 --> 00:16:21.792
Damn it!

00:16:31.625 --> 00:16:33.833
F-Fine, I get it!

00:16:33.833 --> 00:16:35.458
I was wrong!

00:16:35.583 --> 00:16:40.458
I'll leave the guild.
You'll never see me again!

00:16:40.667 --> 00:16:41.875
So...

00:16:42.750 --> 00:16:44.708
I don't want to die!

00:16:52.583 --> 00:16:56.333
You're pretty gullible,
Vice Commander!

00:17:14.583 --> 00:17:17.542
Damn you... You murderer...

00:17:36.750 --> 00:17:38.333
I'm sorry.

00:17:38.583 --> 00:17:40.208
This was...

00:17:40.542 --> 00:17:42.958
This was my fault, right?

00:17:48.792 --> 00:17:50.208
Asuna...

00:17:50.917 --> 00:17:52.542
I'm sorry.

00:17:52.833 --> 00:17:55.458
I sh-should

00:17:56.542 --> 00:17:58.667
stay away from you

00:17:59.542 --> 00:18:03.417
fr-from now on.

00:18:21.458 --> 00:18:24.792
My life belongs to you, Asuna.

00:18:24.792 --> 00:18:29.833
So I'll use it for you.
Let's stay together until the end.

00:18:30.042 --> 00:18:34.250
And I... I'll protect
you too, no matter what.

00:18:34.250 --> 00:18:37.208
I'll protect you forever.

00:18:37.208 --> 00:18:38.625
So...

00:18:38.625 --> 00:18:43.667
I'll see to it that you can go back
to the other world, no matter what.

00:18:44.833 --> 00:18:46.167
Asuna...

00:18:47.167 --> 00:18:48.375
Today...

00:18:49.125 --> 00:18:52.167
Tonight, I want to stay with you.

00:18:56.167 --> 00:18:57.208
Okay.

00:18:57.208 --> 00:18:59.667
"Floor 61: Selmburg"

00:19:12.333 --> 00:19:13.500
Okay.

00:19:37.833 --> 00:19:41.000
D-Don't look over here.

00:19:44.542 --> 00:19:47.750
H-Hurry and get undressed too.

00:19:47.750 --> 00:19:51.750
It's embarrassing,
b-being the only one...

00:19:51.750 --> 00:19:53.708
No, I just...

00:19:53.708 --> 00:19:59.167
I just wanted to s-stay
in the same room tonight...

00:19:59.167 --> 00:20:01.792
That was all...

00:20:12.875 --> 00:20:15.708
Y-Y-You...

00:20:17.917 --> 00:20:19.375
You dummy!

00:20:37.500 --> 00:20:40.125
Sorry, I woke you, didn't I?

00:20:41.208 --> 00:20:45.625
I was just dreaming a little.
About our old world.

00:20:46.500 --> 00:20:48.125
It's strange...

00:20:49.000 --> 00:20:53.625
In the dream, I was worried that
things in Aincrad and things with you

00:20:53.625 --> 00:20:57.500
were only a dream.
I was really scared.

00:20:57.958 --> 00:21:00.750
I'm glad this wasn't a dream.

00:21:00.750 --> 00:21:04.583
You're so strange...
Don't you want to go back?

00:21:04.583 --> 00:21:06.000
I do.

00:21:06.000 --> 00:21:10.792
I do, but I don't want
my time here to disappear.

00:21:11.125 --> 00:21:16.708
These two years have been important
to me. I can think of them that way now.

00:21:19.917 --> 00:21:21.875
Hey, Kirito.

00:21:21.875 --> 00:21:26.500
Do you think it would be okay
if we left the front lines for a bit?

00:21:28.583 --> 00:21:30.375
Somehow, I'm scared.

00:21:30.375 --> 00:21:35.333
If we return to the battlefield, it feels
like something else bad will happen.

00:21:35.333 --> 00:21:38.500
Maybe I'm just a little tired.

00:21:38.667 --> 00:21:40.000
Yeah...

00:21:40.500 --> 00:21:42.625
I'm tired too.

00:21:45.792 --> 00:21:48.417
In the southwest part of floor 22,

00:21:48.417 --> 00:21:52.417
there's a small village
surrounded by forests and lakes.

00:21:52.708 --> 00:21:55.083
Let's move there together.

00:21:55.083 --> 00:21:56.333
And...

00:21:56.917 --> 00:21:58.250
And?

00:22:00.333 --> 00:22:01.500
Let...

00:22:03.000 --> 00:22:05.000
Let's get married.

00:22:14.708 --> 00:22:16.125
Yes!

00:22:30.167 --> 00:22:41.667
<i>The tolling of the faraway bells</i>
<i>sounded a little lonely to me</i>

00:22:42.000 --> 00:22:53.500
<i>So I tried harder, one more time,</i>
<i>this time soaring higher, all the way up</i>

00:22:53.875 --> 00:22:59.417
<i>Neither this reality that just keeps repeating itself</i>

00:22:59.750 --> 00:23:05.250
<i>Nor all my wishes, as numerous as the stars</i>

00:23:05.667 --> 00:23:10.667
<i>Now that I've found the tomorrow</i>
<i>I should strive for</i>

00:23:11.000 --> 00:23:15.958
<i>None of them can overcome these feelings of mine</i>

00:23:16.292 --> 00:23:22.792
<i>A world without end, opening up before my eyes</i>

00:23:23.125 --> 00:23:26.750
<i>Even if it's no more than a dream</i>

00:23:27.292 --> 00:23:34.000
<i>Even if I'm still lost, deep in my heart, it is strong</i>

00:23:34.333 --> 00:23:39.792
<i>Echoing forever and ever</i>

00:23:40.125 --> 00:23:46.333
<i>Shining softly, ever so softly</i>

00:23:47.125 --> 00:23:53.238
Next Time: "The Girl of Morning Dew."
